                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 840.48/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-09T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 9, 1919—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 10—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>163. For the Secretary of State. Sherley reports that the Committee on Rules
                    refused by vote of five to three to grant him a special ruling for the bill
                    appropriating $100,000,000 for relief. He declares without further information
                    he is powerless.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
